President Trump addressed Americans from the Permian Basin in Texas, highlighting the role of the United States in the shale oil and natural gas revolution. He emphasized that his administration has ended the war on American energy by rolling back regulations and unleashing the country's energy resources. The results of this energy dominance include more affordable utilities and gas prices, increased job opportunities, and reduced reliance on foreign energy sources. Shale-driven improvements have also led to a 10% reduction in the global price of oil, saving American consumers $203 billion annually. The United States has become the leading producer of oil and natural gas. Furthermore, President Trump's agenda of energy dominance has positive environmental impacts, with key pollutant concentrations down and carbon dioxide emissions reduced by 15% in the electricity sector. The article highlights that while the left advocates for government mandates, President Trump believes in encouraging American innovation for the benefit of consumers, workers, and the environment.